com.tsgrp.migration.node

Class SimplePropertiesFileNodeWriterListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tsgrp.migration.event.AbstractListener
      • com.tsgrp.migration.node.SimplePropertiesFileNodeWriterListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TargetEndImportNodeEventListener

    public class SimplePropertiesFileNodeWriterListener
extends AbstractListener
implements TargetEndImportNodeEventListener
    Write a file(s) from given node and attributes.

    In general, this class's methods wrap any IOExceptions in ContentExceptions, since the calling Target will not do anything except "fail" when something goes wrong here.

      • getFullFilePath

        protected java.lang.String getFullFilePath(MigrationNode n)
        Construct the full filename of the output file. This defualt implentation uses the injected pathAttr and fileNameAttr to determine the path and base filename; and the injected fileExtension. Subclasses could replace this with alternate logic.
        Parameters:
        n - MigrationNode
        Returns:
        Full path and filename of output file

      • getLineToWrite

        protected java.lang.String getLineToWrite(MigrationNode n,
                                          java.lang.String attrName)
        Construct a single line to write to the output file. This defualt implentation is the standard Java .properties file format, key=value. Subclasses could replace this with alternate logic.
        Parameters:
        n - MigrationNode
        attrName - Attribute to write
        Returns:
        Line to write for given attribute

      • writeFileHeader

        protected void writeFileHeader(java.io.FileWriter fw,
                               MigrationNode n)
        Write any text at the start of the output file, before attributes are listed. This default implementation writes nothing, since no header is needed for a .properties file.
        Parameters:
        fw - Opened FileWriter
        n - Node
